      "review_text": "[h2]Inky Blinky Bob - Review[/h2]\r\n\r\nInky Blinky Bob wants and tries to be a lot of things: a vehicle-based FPS, a survival horror, an open-world RPG and, at times, a quest-based nonlinear adventure and a stealth game. The saying goes: ‘too many chefs spoil the broth’, and in this case, perhaps ‘too many genres spoil the game’. In some ways, this mish-mash of genres actually works pretty well; in others, much less so. It’s good and all to experiment and blend things together to craft a fine mix, much like cocktails; however, even for the most experienced studios, never mind an Indie one on their first Steam release, this would be a daunting task. The result of great ambitions and only passable execution is still better than most similar cases: a game that works and plays out just well enough to be passable, but not nearly well enough to be actually good, let alone great.\r\n\r\n[b]The full review was written for Summit Reviews' website, you can find it [url=https://summitreviews.biz/article/71/inky-blinky-bob-review]here[/url][/b]\r\n\r\nFollow the [url=https://store.steampowered.com/curator/41449676/]Summit Reviews Curator[/url] and [url=https://summitreviews.biz]Website[/url] to see more high-quality reviews regularly.",
      "timestamp_created": 1774036667
    },
