      "votes_up": 1,
      "playtime_at_review": 222,
      "review_text": "When I saw the trailer for this game I thought it'd be too good to be true, but having almost beaten it at this point I want to leave an \"early\" review and just say it's a blast. The writing is simple and funny and straight to the point, the gameplay is varied and satisfying and it lasts you for a few hours. For being an indie title, this game gave so much more than I expected and looks absolutely stellar. With so many different elements in the game it could've ended up too chaotic, but I feel like the devs found a pretty good balance for everything. I found a few bugs during my own stream, but the devs saw it and instantly made a point to get it fixed either today or tomorrow, so they're eager to make sure any potential bugs are stomped out fast. W devs!",
